{"title_page": "199Quad", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=April 2010}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = 199Quad\n| type       = Album\n| artist     = [[69 Boyz]]\n| cover      = 199Quad.jpg\n| alt        = A fully naked woman stretches out for a pose while the band's name (written in gold lettering) and the album title (written in grey lettering) cover the front and bottom parts of her body.\n| released   = {{Start date|1994|05|27}}\n| recorded   = 1993-1994\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]], [[miami bass]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=74|s=10}}\n| label      = Rip-it\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[The Wait is Over]]\n| next_year  = 1998\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = 199Quad\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Tootsee Roll]]\n | single1date = May 31, 1994\n | single2     = Kitty Kitty\n | single2date = 1994\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score =  {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r203094|pure_url=yes}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''199Quad''''' is the debut album of the [[Southern rap]] group [[69 Boyz]], released in 1994 following the success of their song \"[[Tootsee Roll]]\".  The album peaked at number 59 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] on April 1, 1995. The album was re-released with a new cover and a bonus DVD by [[Lil Joe]] on October 10, 2006. On July 11, 1995, the album was certified Platinum by the RIAA for selling 1,000,000 copies.{{Certification Cite Ref|title=Nineteen Ninety Quad|artist=69 Boyz|type=album|region=United States}}\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Tracklist\n| all_writing = Da S.W.A.T. Team (Jay McGowan and Van Bryant)\n| total_length = 74:10\n| title1 = Land 69\n| length1 = 1:07\n| title2 = Caller #10\n| length2 = 0:47\n| title3 = Da Train\n| length3 = 4:29\n| title4 = Loose Booty\n| length4 = 4:07\n| title5 = Kitty Kitty\n| length5 = 4:10\n| title6 = Puddin Tame\n| length6 = 3:29\n| title7 = Da Set\n| length7 = 2:25\n|